# meh-tabs — Firefox Extensions Repo

## What lives here

Two related Firefox MV2 extensions in the same repo:

1. **Custom New Tab** (this directory, root) — new-tab replacement: clock, stopwatch,
   todo list, link categories, tab sorting, Chordify extraction, entertainment-tab
   window moving, config editor.
2. **Page Date Overlay** (`page-date-overlay/`) — content-script-based overlay that
   shows publication date / author on every page visited. See
   [docs/page-date-overlay.md](docs/page-date-overlay.md) for the full product doc.

## Extension security rules (BOTH extensions)

- Follow Firefox extension security policies — no inline CSS styles, no `onclick`
  handlers, no remote scripts. Do not add CSP overrides to paper over violations;
  write the code properly.
- AMO validation rules:
  - No remote scripts; all JS bundled locally.
  - Prefer DOM methods (`createElement`, `textContent`) over `innerHTML` for any
    value that could come from remote content.
  - `browser_specific_settings.gecko.data_collection_permissions.required`
    must be `["none"]` (not `[]`) if the extension collects no data.
  - Version in `manifest.json` must strictly increase for AMO uploads.

## Working with me

- If a directive is unclear or you need more info or options, ask.
- When doing substantial changes, report what you changed and any drift
  between docs and code.

## Custom New Tab — structure

```
newtab.html            Main page
newtab.js              Core: ConfigManager, Stopwatch, EntertainmentManager, wiring
todo.js                TodoList (localStorage, SortableJS drag-and-drop)
background.js          Tab sort, Chordify extraction, entertainment moving
styles.css             Custom styles
bootstrap.min.css      Bootstrap 5 CSS (local)
bootstrap.bundle.min.js Bootstrap 5 JS (local, required by AMO)
Sortable.min.js        Sortable (local, required by AMO)
icons/                 32/48/96/128 PNG icons
links.json.example     Example config
personal-config.json   Personal config (gitignored)
dist/                  Signed XPI builds
build-and-sign.ps1     AMO upload + signing helper
tools/package.py       Packaging helper
tools-generate-icons.py  Icon generation
```

## Page Date Overlay — structure (see docs/page-date-overlay.md)

```
page-date-overlay/
├── manifest.json
├── background.js         Wayback Machine + Last-Modified HEAD + messaging
├── content/
│   ├── extractor.js      Tier 1-3 signal extractors (meta, JSON-LD, URL, text)
│   ├── overlay.js        Shadow-DOM overlay UI, edit/override, type picker
│   └── overlay.css       Overlay styles (injected into shadow root)
├── newtab/               Optional dashboard (reading history, rules)
│   ├── index.html
│   └── index.js
├── common/
│   ├── storage.js        pageMeta / typeRules / settings helpers
│   └── url.js            URL normalization
└── icons/
```

## Conventions (BOTH extensions)

- Keep dependencies minimal. No new frameworks; Bootstrap + Sortable is it.
- Performance matters, especially on the new-tab page and content script
  (runs on every page load).
- User data stays local; never send page content off the machine without
  explicit per-call user opt-in.
- No inline styles or inline event handlers; separate CSS files; wire events
  via `addEventListener` from JS.
- Comments should explain intent or non-obvious constraints, not narrate code.
